CatDescriptText: Cutline of image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, November 29, 1952, pg. 6 reads: "They Danced For Community Chest - For the second straight year, the Palsetta Club of Beltzhoover held its annual benefit at Knoxville Junior High School to entertain the members of their community and raise funds for the Community Chest Drive. The affair, entitled "The Toast of the Town." was held last Wednesday evening.  According to officers, "Every penny above expenses for the show annually goes to the Community Chest effort."  One of the best examples of this year's show was this "Can-Can" number. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Young women wearing can can dance costumes, including Lois Jean Dougan on front end, performing on stage in Knoxville Junior High School for "Toast of the Town" Community Chest benefit drive sponsored by Palsetta Club
